ZH: 那条运河是一个连接两个城市的重要交通通道。
EN: That canal is an important transportation channel connecting two cities.

ZH: 运河上有很多游船，可以供游客乘坐。
EN: There are many tourist boats on the canal for visitors to ride on.

ZH: 这座城市因为有一条运河而闻名于世。
EN: This city is famous worldwide for having a canal.

ZH: 这条运河的建设需要大量的人力和物力。
EN: The construction of this canal requires a lot of labor and materials.

ZH: 运河的开放让城市的经济得以快速发展。
EN: The opening of the canal has allowed the city's economy to develop rapidly.

ZH: 这条运河是由人工挖掘出来的。
EN: This canal was dug by hand.

ZH: 这座城市的运河历史悠久，始建于几百年前。
EN: The canal in this city has a long history, dating back several hundred years.

ZH: 这条运河的长度超过了500公里。
EN: The length of this canal exceeds 500 kilometers.

ZH: 运河两旁种满了美丽的垂柳树。
EN: Beautiful weeping willow trees are planted along both sides of the canal.

ZH: 沿着运河散步是一种愉快的方式来放松身心。
EN: Taking a walk along the canal is a pleasant way to relax.

ZH: 运河的水是蓝蓝的，非常清澈。
EN: The water in the canal is blue and very clear.

ZH: 运河上的船只络绎不绝，繁忙而壮观。
EN: The boats on the canal are constantly coming and going, busy and spectacular.

ZH: 这座城市的运河是世界遗产之一。
EN: The canal in this city is one of the world heritages.

ZH: 运河的两岸是一片美丽的风景，吸引了很多游客。
EN: The two banks of the canal are a beautiful sight, attracting many tourists.

ZH: 这条运河是人们进行农产品运输的重要通道。
EN: This canal is an important channel for transporting agricultural products.

ZH: 运河上有很多小船，人们可以划船在上面玩耍。
EN: There are many small boats on the canal for people to paddle and play.

ZH: 运河的两侧是繁华的商业区，有很多商店和餐馆。
EN: The two sides of the canal are bustling commercial areas with many shops and restaurants.

ZH: 这个城市的景点中有一处古老的运河码头。
EN: One of the attractions in this city is an ancient canal wharf.

ZH: 这条运河贯穿了整个城市，成为了城市的标志之一。
EN: This canal runs through the entire city and has become one of its landmarks.

ZH: 运河上有一座古老的石桥，历经百年仍然安然立在那里。
EN: There is an ancient stone bridge on the canal, standing there unscathed after a century.
